{"title_page": "Sangita Madhavan Nair", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian actress}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Sangita Madhavan Nair\n| image              = Sangita_Madhavan_Nair.jpg\n| imagesize          = \n| caption            = Actress Sangeetha in 2013\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1976|07|25}}\n| birth_place        = [[India]]\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| othername          = \n| occupation         = Actress\n| yearsactive        = 1978\u20132003;\n2014\n| spouse             = [[S. Saravanan]] (m.2000 - present)\n| children           = Saai Thejaswathy (b.2002)\n| parents            = Madhavan Nair<br>Padma\n| website            = \n| notable role       = \n}}\n\n'''Sangeetha''' is an [[India]]n actress, who has worked in [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Kannada]] and [[Malayalam]] film industries, predominantly in the 1990s.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.jointscene.com/artists/Kollywood/Sangita/15949 |title=Archived copy |access-date=15 April 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111007024132/http://www.jointscene.com/artists/Kollywood/Sangita/15949 |archive-date=7 October 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The actress is best known for her role as '''''Shyamala''''' in ''[[Chinthavishtayaya Shyamala]]'', which was written and directed by [[Sreenivasan]].<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sreenivasan-sangita-rejoin-after-chinthavishtayaya-shyamala-607231 | title=Sreenivasan and Sangita to Rejoin After 'Chinthavishtayaya Shyamala' | date=20 August 2014 | first=Nicy | last=V.P. | newspaper=International Business Times | accessdate=2 April 2019 }}</ref> She is also well known for her role of Nirmala Mary in actor [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]]'s breakthrough film ''[[Poove Unakkaga]]'' (1996).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-05-20/regional/28302528_1_wedding-reception-kollywood-stars-kb|title=Sudharsan's starry wedding reception - Times of India|publisher=|accessdate=18 July 2018}}</ref> She started her career as a child artiste in the movie ''Snehikkan Oru Pennu'', a Malayalam movie released in 1978. Her debut film as a child artist in Tamil was ''[[En Rathathin Rathame]]'', which is the Tamil remake of Hindi movie ''[[Mr. India (1987 film)|Mr. India]]''. The first film she acted as a heroine was ''[[Ellame En Rasathan]]'' in 1995.\n\n==Personal life==\nShe is born as the youngest among four children, to Madhavan Nair from [[Kottakkal]], [[Malappuram]] and mother, Padma, a Tamilian, from [[Kuzhalmannam (gram panchayat)|Kuzhalmannam]], [[Palakkad]], settled in [[Chennai]]. Her father migrated to [[Chennai]] for fruit business and the family settled there. She had her primary education from Sri Gujarati Vid Matriculation School, [[Chennai]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mangalam.com/cinema/interviews/235471?page=0,0 |title=Archived copy |access-date=5 October 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006085944/http://www.mangalam.com/cinema/interviews/235471?page=0,0 |archive-date=6 October 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> She has two sisters, Mallika and Charu and a brother, Nitheesh.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mangalam.com/mangalam-varika/233929?page=0,0 |title=Archived copy |access-date=30 September 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141004055036/http://www.mangalam.com/mangalam-varika/233929?page=0,0 |archive-date=4 October 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Her brother portrayed a supporting role in her unreleased film, ''Punniyavathi''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/soc.culture.tamil/i_HDqNg7Dmo|title=Google Groups|website=Groups.google.com|accessdate=18 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nShe married cinematographer [[S. Saravanan]] in 2000 and retired from acting after marriage. She assisted her husband when he directed his first film, ''[[Silambattam (film)|Silambattam]]'' starring [[Silambarasan]], [[Sana Khan]] and [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/33129.html|title=Tamil Cinema News - Tamil Movie Reviews - Tamil Movie Trailers|website=Indiaglitz.com|accessdate=18 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/feb-07-02/16-02-07-simbu.html|title=Movie News simbu silambaattam saravanan sangeetha nayantara liplock simbu nayantara kiss simbu nayan gallery images|website=Behindwoods.com|accessdate=18 July 2018}}</ref> They have a daughter, Saai Thejaswathy.\n\n==Awards==\n* 1996 - Nominated - [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Tamil]] - [[Poove Unakkaga]]\n* 1998 - [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Actress]] \u2013 [[Chinthavishtayaya Shyamala]]\n* 1998 - Nominated \u2013 [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Malayalam]] - [[Chinthavishtayaya Shyamala]]\n* 1998 - Nominated \u2013 '''Asianet Film award for best actress''' \u2013 [[Chinthavishtayaya Shyamala]]\n* 1998 - Cinema Express Award for Best Actress (Malayalam) \u2013 [[Chinthavishtayaya Shyamala]]\n\n== Partial filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#000;\"\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Language !!class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n| 1978 || ''[[Snehikkan Oru Pennu]]'' || || Malayalam ||Child Artiste\n|-\n| 1983 || ''[[Manju (film)|Manju]]'' || || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1986 || ''[[Vartha]]'' || || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| ''[[Ennennum Kannettante]]'' || || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| 1987 || ''Nee Allenkil Njan'' || || Malayalam||\n|-\n|1989|| ''[[En Rathathin Rathame]]'' || || Tamil||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"|1990 ||  ''Vazhndhu Kattuvom'' ||  || [[Tamil language|Tamil]] ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"|1991 ||  ''[[Idhaya Vaasal]]'' || Uma  || Tamil ||\n|-\n|  ''[[Shanti Kranti (1991 Kannada film)|Shanti Kranti]]'' || ||[[Kannada]]||\n|-\n|  ''[[Kadinjool Kalyanam]]'' || || Malayalam ||\n|-\n|  ''[[Nattukku Oru Nallavan]]'' ||   || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Neelagiri (film)|Neelagiri]]''  || || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"|1992 || ''[[Naangal]]'' ||Gayathri   || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''Devar Veettu Ponnu'' ||  || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Chinna Pasanga Naanga]]'' ||  || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''Vasantha Malargal'' ||  || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Samundi]]'' || Lakshmi  || Tamil ||\n|-\n|  ''[[Naadody (1992 film)|Naadody]]'' || Sindhu || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| 1993 || ''[[Arthana]]'' ||Anu|| Malayalam||\n|-\n| 1993 || ''[[Thalattu]]'' ||Sangita|  ||Tamil\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"|1994 ||  ''[[Mahanadi (film)|Mahanadi]]'' || Adult Kaveri || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Sarigamapadani]]'' || Sangita || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Raja Pandi]]'' ||  || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Ravanan (1994 film)|Ravanan]]'' ||Uma ||Tamil||\n|-\n| ''Pudhusa Pootha Rosa'' ||  || Tamil ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\"|1995 ||  ''[[Simhavalan Menon]]'' ||  Urmila || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| ''Manathile Oru Paattu'' || || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Ellame En Rasathan]]'' || Raani || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Pullakuttikaran]]'' ||Ammu || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''Swapnam''  || || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| ''[[Seethanam]]'' || Dhanalakshmi || Tamil ||\n|-\n|''[[Aniyan Bava Chetan Bava]]'' || Malu|| Malayalam ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\"|1996 ||  ''[[Amman Kovil Vaasalile]]'' ||  Poongothai|| Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Poove Unakkaga]]'' || Nirmala Mary || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Puthiya Parasakthi]]'' ||  || Tamil ||\n|-\n|  ''[[Kaalam Maari Pochu (1996 film)|Kaalam Maari Pochu]]'' || Indra || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''Vetri Vinayagar'' || Asirikai || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Namma Ooru Raasa]]'' ||  Raasathi|| Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Alexander (1996 film)|Alexander]]'' || Priya || Tamil ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"|1997 || ''[[Vallal]]'' || Chella Kili || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Ganga Gowri (1997 film)|Ganga Gowri]]'' || Gowri || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''Adrasakkai Adrasakkai'' || Sangeetha|| Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Pongalo Pongal]]'' || Chitra || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''Punniyavathi'' ||  || Tamil || Unreleased\n|-\n| ''[[Kalyana Vaibhogam]]'' || Shanthi || Tamil ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"|1998 || ''[[Kattathoru Penpoovu]]'' || Kasthuri || Malayalam || \n|-\n| ''[[Rathna (film)|Rathna]]'' || Chinthamani || Tamil || \n|-\n| ''[[Chinthavishtayaya Shyamala]]'' || Shyamala || Malayalam || [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Actress]] <br>Most Popular Role \n|-\n| ''[[Manthrikumaran]]''  || Aswathy|| Malayalam || \n|-\n| ''[[Yaare Neenu Cheluve]]'' || Kamali || [[Kannada]] ||\n|-\n|''[[Kumbakonam Gopalu]]''||Sangeetha||Tamil||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"8\"|1999 || ''[[Samarasimha Reddy]]'' || Sangeetha || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] ||\n|-\n| ''[[Ethirum Pudhirum]]'' || Selvi || Tamil || \n|-\n| ''[[Poomaname Vaa]]'' ||  Seetha|| Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Pallavur Devanarayanan]]'' || Vasundhara || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| ''[[Vazhunnor]]'' || Rabeka || Malayalam || \n|-\n| ''[[Crime File]]'' || Amala || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| ''[[Saaphalyam]]'' ||Sumithra || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| ''[[Jayam (1999 film)|Jayam]]'' || Durga || Tamil ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2000|| ''[[Yare Nee Abhimani]]'' || Utthara|| Kannada ||\n|-\n| ''[[Kann Thirandhu Paaramma]]'' || Gayatri, Amman || Tamil || \n|-\n| 2002 || ''[[Kanal Kireedam]]'' ||Mary || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Nagara Varidhi Naduvil Njan]]'' || Sunitha || Malayalam ||\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|4971633}}\n*[http://en.msidb.org/displayProfile.php?category=actors&artist=Sangeetha&limit=24 Sangita at MSI]\n\n{{KeralaStateAwardForBestActress}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Madhavan Nair, Sangita}}\n[[Category:Indian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Telugu cinema]]\n[[Category:Kerala State Film Award winners]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Tamil cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses in Malayalam cinema]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Kerala]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian actresses]]\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:People from Malappuram district]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Chennai]]\n\n\n{{India-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian actress}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name =  Sangita\n| image =\n| imagesize =\n| caption = Actress Sangeetha at Tamil Lyricist Piraisudan's daughter wedding reception in 2013\n| birth_name = \n| birth_date  = \n| birth_place =\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| othername =\n| occupation = Actress\n| yearsactive = 1978\u20132003;\n2014\n| spouse = [[S. Saravanan]] (m.2000 - present)\n| children = Saai Thejaswathy (b.2002)\n| parents = Madhavan Nair<br>Padma\n| website =\n| notable role =\n}}\n\n'''Sangeetha''' is an [[India]]n actress, who has worked in [[Tamil language|Tamil]], [[Kannada]] and [[Malayalam]] film industries, predominantly in the 1990s.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.jointscene.com/artists/Kollywood/Sangita/15949 |title=Archived copy |access-date=15 April 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111007024132/http://www.jointscene.com/artists/Kollywood/Sangita/15949 |archive-date=7 October 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> The actress is best known for her role as '''''Shyamala''''' in ''[[Chinthavishtayaya Shyamala]]'', which was written and directed by [[Sreenivasan]].<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/sreenivasan-sangita-rejoin-after-chinthavishtayaya-shyamala-607231 | title=Sreenivasan and Sangita to Rejoin After 'Chinthavishtayaya Shyamala' | date=20 August 2014 | first=Nicy | last=V.P. | newspaper=International Business Times | accessdate=2 April 2019 }}</ref> She is also well known for her role of Nirmala Mary in actor [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]]'s breakthrough film ''[[Poove Unakkaga]]'' (1996).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-05-20/regional/28302528_1_wedding-reception-kollywood-stars-kb|title=Sudharsan's starry wedding reception - Times of India|publisher=|accessdate=18 July 2018}}</ref> She started her career as a child artiste in the movie ''Snehikkan Oru Pennu'', a Malayalam movie released in 1978. Her debut film as a child artist in Tamil was ''[[En Rathathin Rathame]]'', which is the Tamil remake of Hindi movie ''[[Mr. India (1987 film)|Mr. India]]''. The first film she acted as a heroine was ''[[Ellame En Rasathan]]'' in 1995.\n\n==Personal life==\nShe is born as the youngest among four children, to Madhavan Nair from [[Kottakkal]], [[Malappuram]] and mother, Padma, a Tamilian, from [[Kuzhalmannam (gram panchayat)|Kuzhalmannam]], [[Palakkad]], settled in [[Chennai]]. Her father migrated to [[Chennai]] for fruit business and the family settled there. She had her primary education from Sri Gujarati Vid Matriculation School, [[Chennai]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mangalam.com/cinema/interviews/235471?page=0,0 |title=Archived copy |access-date=5 October 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006085944/http://www.mangalam.com/cinema/interviews/235471?page=0,0 |archive-date=6 October 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> She has two sisters, Mallika and Charu and a brother, Nitheesh.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mangalam.com/mangalam-varika/233929?page=0,0 |title=Archived copy |access-date=30 September 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141004055036/http://www.mangalam.com/mangalam-varika/233929?page=0,0 |archive-date=4 October 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Her brother portrayed a supporting role in her unreleased film, ''Punniyavathi''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/soc.culture.tamil/i_HDqNg7Dmo|title=Google Groups|website=Groups.google.com|accessdate=18 July 2018}}</ref>\n\nShe married cinematographer [[S. Saravanan]] in 2000 and retired from acting after marriage. She assisted her husband when he directed his first film, ''[[Silambattam (film)|Silambattam]]'' starring [[Silambarasan]], [[Sana Khan]] and [[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/33129.html|title=Tamil Cinema News - Tamil Movie Reviews - Tamil Movie Trailers|website=Indiaglitz.com|accessdate=18 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news/feb-07-02/16-02-07-simbu.html|title=Movie News simbu silambaattam saravanan sangeetha nayantara liplock simbu nayantara kiss simbu nayan gallery images|website=Behindwoods.com|accessdate=18 July 2018}}</ref> They have a daughter, Saai Thejaswathy.\n\n==Awards==\n* 1996 - Nominated - [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Tamil]] - [[Poove Unakkaga]]\n* 1998 - [[Kerala State Film Award for Best Actress]] \u2013 [[Chinthavishtayaya Shyamala]]\n* 1998 - Nominated \u2013 [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress \u2013 Malayalam]] - [[Chinthavishtayaya Shyamala]]\n* 1998 - Nominated \u2013 '''Asianet Film award for best actress''' \u2013 [[Chinthavishtayaya Shyamala]]\n* 1998 - Cinema Express Award for Best Actress (Malayalam) \u2013 [[Chinthavishtayaya Shyamala]]\n\n== Partial filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#000;\"\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Language !!class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n| 1978 || ''[[Snehikkan Oru Pennu]]'' || || Malayalam ||Child Artiste\n|-\n| 1983 || ''[[Manju (film)|Manju]]'' || || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 1986 || ''[[Vartha]]'' || || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| ''[[Ennennum Kannettante]]'' || || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| 1987 || ''Nee Allenkil Njan'' || || Malayalam||\n|-\n|1989|| ''[[En Rathathin Rathame]]'' || || Tamil||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"|1990 ||  ''Vazhndhu Kattuvom'' ||  || [[Tamil language|Tamil]] ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"|1991 ||  ''[[Idhaya Vaasal]]'' || Uma  || Tamil ||\n|-\n|  ''[[Shanti Kranti (1991 Kannada film)|Shanti Kranti]]'' || ||[[Kannada]]||\n|-\n|  ''[[Kadinjool Kalyanam]]'' || || Malayalam ||\n|-\n|  ''[[Nattukku Oru Nallavan]]'' ||   || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Neelagiri (film)|Neelagiri]]''  || || Malayalam ||\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"|1992 || ''[[Naangal]]'' ||Gayathri   || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''Devar Veettu Ponnu'' ||  || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''[[Chinna Pasanga Naanga]]'' ||  || Tamil ||\n|-\n| ''Vasantha Malargal'' ||  